{
  "text": "In single camera multi-objects tracking (SCT), the prediction of the spatio-temporal information of objects is more reliable and the appearance of objects does not have much variation during tracking. This makes the SCT task less challenge than the ICT task. i. e. For some less challenge videos, a simple appearance representation (e.g. color histogram [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] ) works well. The graphic model are often used to solve different problems, such as occlusion [CITATION_4] , [CITATION_5] , crowd [CITATION_6] , [CITATION_7] and interference of appearance similarity [CITATION_8] , [CITATION_9] . However, for challenge videos, These approach led to frequent id-switch errors and trajectory fragmentation.",
  "correct_citation": {
